label.value: Culdoscopy

value.value: Endoscopic examination of a woman's pelvic organs using a culdoscope inserted through the vagina.

label.value: 14-3-3 Protein Zeta/Delta

value.value: 14-3-3 protein zeta/delta (245 aa, ~28 kDa) is encoded by the human YWHAZ gene. This protein is involved in both signaling and phosphoserine binding.

label.value: Base Number

value.value: A positive integer (sometimes called the radix or scale) that establishes the counting numbers and place values in a number system.

label.value: Coat

value.value: The covering of hair, wool, or fur on the body of an animal.

label.value: Operation

value.value: Performance of a practical work or of something involving the practical application of principles or processes.

label.value: Generation

value.value: A single step in the line of descent from a common ancestor.

label.value: LAPTM4B Gene

value.value: This gene may play a role in transport processes.

label.value: LAPTM4B wt Allele

value.value: Human LAPTM4B wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q22.1 and is approximately 146 kb in length. This allele, which encodes lysosomal-associated transmembrane protein 4B, may be involved in transport. Amplification of the gene may be associated with hepatocellular carcinoma and both anthracycline resistance and metastatic recurrence in breast cancer.

label.value: Lysosomal-Associated Transmembrane Protein 4B

value.value: Lysosomal-associated transmembrane protein 4B (370 aa, ~41 kDa) is encoded by the human LAPTM4B gene. This protein may play a role in transport.

label.value: MDM4 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in both cell cycle arrest and the inhibition of apoptosis.

label.value: MDM4 wt Allele

value.value: Human MDM4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q32 and is approximately 34 kb in length. This allele, which encodes protein Mdm4, is involved in cell cycle checkpoint regulation. Aberrant gene expression is associated with retinoblastoma.

label.value: Metastatic Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor

value.value: The presence of malignant Schwann cell growth (benign variant is known as neurofibroma) at a site removed from the primary site of tumor growth.

label.value: Protein Mdm4

value.value: Protein Mdm4 (490 aa, ~55 kDa) is encoded by the human MDM4 gene. This protein plays a role in the mediation of cell cycle arrest.

label.value: CARM1 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in both chromatin remodeling and protein methylation.

label.value: CARM1 wt Allele

value.value: Human CARM1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 19p13.2 and is approximately 51 kb in length. This allele, which encodes histone-arginine methyltransferase CARM1 protein, plays a role in transcription regulation, protein methylation and chromatin remodeling. Aberrant expression of the gene is associated with both prostate adenocarcinomas and high-grade prostatic intraepithelial neoplasia.

label.value: Histone-Arginine Methyltransferase CARM1

value.value: Histone-arginine methyltransferase CARM1 (585 aa, ~63 kDa) is encoded by the human CARM1 gene. This protein is involved in the mediation of protein methylation that, in turn, regulates both chromatin organization and transcription.

label.value: Serum Cystatin C Assay

value.value: An immunoassay used for the measurement of cystatin-C levels in the serum to determine the glomerular filtration rate.

label.value: Urinary Creatinine Assay

value.value: A laboratory test used for the measurement of creatinine levels in the urine to determine the degree of renal dysfunction.

label.value: Urinary Microalbumin Assay

value.value: An immunoassay used for the measurement of microalbumin levels in the urine to determine the glomerular filtration rate.

label.value: Serum Creatinine Assay

value.value: A laboratory test used for the measurement of creatinine levels in the serum to determine the glomerular filtration rate.

label.value: Primary Cutaneous Lymphoma TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of primary cutaneous lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM v7 classification system.  Mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome have a formal staging system proposed by the International Society for Cutaneous Lymphomas (ISCL) and EORTC.  The other cutaneous non-Hodgkin lymphomas are staged using the same system for lymphomas presenting in other anatomic locations.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Recurrent Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor

value.value: The reemergence of malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumor after a period of remission.

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome Primary Tumor-Skin TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor (skin).

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome TX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Primary tumor cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome T1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Limited patches, papules, and/or plaques covering less than 10% of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T1a (patch only) vs. T1b (plaque +/- patch).  Note: for skin, patch indicates any size skin lesion without significant elevation or induration.  Presence/absence of hypo- or hyperpigmentation, scale, crusting, and/or poikiloderma should be noted.  Plaque indicates any size skin lesion that is elevated or indurated.  Presence or absence of scale, crusting, and/or poikiloderma should be noted.  Histologic features such as folliculotropism or large-cell transformation (more than 25% large cells), CD30+ or CD30-, and clinical features such as ulceration are important to document.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome T2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Patches, papules, or plaques covering 10% or more of the skin surface.  May further stratify into T2a (patch only) vs. T2b (plaque +/- patch).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome T3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: One or more tumors (equal or greater than 1 cm diameter).  Note: for skin, tumor indicates at least 1 cm diameter solid or nodular lesion with evidence of depth and/or vertical growth.  Note total number of lesions, total volume of lesions, largest size lesion, and region of body involved.  Also note if histologic evidence of large-cell transformation has occurred.  Phenotyping for CD30 is encouraged.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome T4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Confluence of erythema covering 80% or more of body surface area.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of peripheral lymph nodes.

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: No clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; biopsy not required.  Note: for node, abnormal peripheral lymph node(s) indicates any palpable peripheral node that on physical examination is firm, irregular, clustered, fixed or 1.5 cm or larger in diameter.  Node groups examined on physical examination include cervical, supraclavicular, epitrochlear, axillary, and inguinal.  Central nodes, which are not generally amenable to pathologic assessment, are not currently considered in the nodal classification unless used to establish N3 histopathology.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 1 or NCI LN0-2.  Note: Dutch grade 1: dermatopathic lymphadenopathy.  NCI LN0: no atypical lymphocytes.  NCI LN1: occasional and isolated atypical lymphocytes (not arranged in clusters).  NCI LN2: many atypical lymphocytes or in 3-6 cell clusters.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone negative.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Recurrent Rhabdomyosarcoma

value.value: The reemergence of rhabdomyosarcoma after a period of remission.

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone positive.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grade 2 or NCI LN3.  Note: Dutch grade 2: dermatopathic lymphadenopathy; early involvement by mycosis fungoides (presence of cerebriform nuclei greater than 7.5 micrometers).  NCI LN3: aggregates of atypical lymphocytes; nodal architecture preserved.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone negative.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone positive.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome N3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; histopathology Dutch grades 3-4 or NCI LN4; clone positive or negative.  Note: Dutch grade 3: partial effacement of lymph node architecture; many atypical cerebriform mononuclear cells (CMCs).  Dutch grade 4: complete effacement of lymph node. NCI LN4: partial/complete effacement of nodal architecture by atypical lymphocytes or frankly neoplastic cells.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome NX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clinically abnormal peripheral lymph nodes; no histologic confirmation.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome Distant Metastasis-Visceral TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases (visceral). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome M0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: No visceral organ involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome M1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Visceral involvement (must have pathology confirmation and organ involved should be specified).  Note: for viscera, spleen and liver may be diagnosed by imaging criteria. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome Peripheral Blood Involvement TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of mycosis fungoides and Sezary syndrome, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to peripheral blood involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Metastatic Synovial Sarcoma

value.value: A synovial sarcoma that has metastasized to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome B0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Absence of significant blood involvement: 5% or less of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary cells).  Note: for blood, Sezary cells are defined as lymphocytes with hyperconvoluted cerebriform nuclei.  If Sezary cells are not able to be used to determine tumor burden for B2, then one of the following modified ISCL criteria along with a positive clonal rearrangement of the TCR may be used instead: (1) expanded CD4+ or CD3+ cells with CD4/CD8 ratio of 10 or more, (2) expanded CD4+ cells with abnormal immunophenotype including loss of CD7 or CD26. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome B0a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone negative.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome B0b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone positive.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome B1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Low blood tumor burden: more than 5% of peripheral blood lymphocytes are atypical (Sezary) cells but does not meet the criteria of B2. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mycosis Fungoides and Sezary Syndrome B1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Clone negative.  Note: A T-cell clone is defined by PCR or Southern blot analysis of the T-cell receptor gene.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
